256	        // HIGH-1: Atomically consume single-use links BEFORE decrypting/serving content.
257	        // consumeLink() uses SELECT FOR UPDATE in a transaction — concurrent-safe.
258	        // If consumption fails (race loser: already consumed by a concurrent request), throw
